Rashford: ‚ÄúThe mental state of the players and staff is positive, we go there to win the game. With that mindset and the spirit we have, anything is possible." [@laura_woodsy, @psmithXI]

Rashford on Chelsea: ‚ÄúWe've got things that can hurt them, we've got players who can hurt them, as long as we're together and choose the right moments to go we'll be fine.‚Äù [@laura_woodsy, @psmithX]

Rashford: ‚ÄúTactically the manager [Thomas Tuchel] is a very good manager. We played against him a few times when he was at Paris St-Germain and tactically he was good in those games as well.‚Äù [@laura_woodsy, @psmithXI] https://t.co/UD6LrsaBcX

Rashford: ‚ÄúThe players are finding it within ourselves to give 110% and we're going to have to keep doing that. We know we're in an uphill battle but everyone's ready for the fight and we don't have anyone in our team who is shying away from that.‚Äú [@laura_woodsy, @psmithXI]

Rashford on Carrick: ‚ÄúA lot of the principles have stayed the same because they're the principles that got us so close to winning those trophies. Not much has changed.‚Äù [@laura_woodsy, @psmithXI] https://t.co/hDNwkooXsu
Rashford: ‚ÄúWe all stuck together, we dug in deep. They're a good team and keep the ball a lot and we found a way to win the game." [@laura_woodsy, @psmithXI]
Rashford on Solskjaer: ‚ÄúOne of the things Ole always said to us was, 'when you're on the pitch, stick together'. And that performance against Villarreal was that.‚Äù [@laura_woodsy, @psmithXI]
Rashford on Solskjaer: ‚ÄúInside you feel guilty because everybody has a role to play when you're on the pitch.‚Äù [@laura_woodsy, @psmithXI]

Rashford: ‚ÄúIf those moments go our way, we could end up with two or three trophies, maybe he'd have had more time. But it's football, things happen, and you can only move on from it. Even though it's difficult, you have to find a way to move on." [@laura_woodsy, @psmithXI] https://t.co/5YQWtKIzTW

Rashford on Solskjaer: ‚ÄúThe way it started, the position he brought us to, we were close a couple of times to winning big trophies and we always seemed to just fall short.‚Äù [@laura_woodsy, @psmithXI] https://t.co/ttiF8rOJER
Rashford: ‚ÄúOle knows he'll always be a legend of this club and the players here respect him 100 per cent. It's unfortunate that it didn't go our way as a group.‚Äù [@laura_woodsy, @psmithXI]

Rashford on Solskjaer: ‚ÄúI've been here when managers have left and they just pack their stuff and go out the door. But it just shows how good a person he is, how much the club means to him.‚Äù [@laura_woodsy, @psmithXI]
Rashford on Solskjaer‚Äôs exit: "[He spoke to us] individually, around breakfast time, then we had a meeting before we went out to train, which was very different.‚Äù [@laura_woodsy, @psmithXI]

3 goals 1 conceded (shit penalty), 1 clean sheet, 1st in the group and a point away at Chelsea. Much better situation for Rangnick to take hold of. Carricks done his job.

Varane will return soon, Bailly and Lindelof both excellent so I‚Äôm feeling better about our CBs. Recalling Laird or making a purchase at RB in January seems necessary. Getting a midfielder in January would be a dream.

Anyway, a very strong defensive performance and I really liked our play in the second half. I don‚Äôt see a title charge at United but riding this strength into Arsenal could put us comfortably back around top 4. Think we can be dangerous in tournament play.

My point is more that both could definitely be pens. It‚Äôs weird how fouls that have no effect on the play get called but softer fouls that prevent a goal scoring chance are let go. Both would likely be fouls outside the box so why is only one called inside?

My argument on the pen is Rudigers slight blocking off of Fred in the first half prevents a goal scoring chance and is often a foul outside the box while AWBs attempted clearance has no real effect on the play.
